Diagnostic characters: (
1
) tegmina with white patch along sutural margin on nodal line of cross-veins (Fig. 8 A); (
2
) legs I and II dark brown with pale yellow rings (Fig. 8 E); (
3
) tegmina marked with numerous small black-brown spots, some of them v-shaped on veins (Fig. 8 A); (
4
) disc of hind wings orange with base red, rarely completely orange-red, with 6–15 black spots in 3 rows and 4 ( 3–5 ) small white spots (Fig. 8 A); (
5
) abdominal tergites red (Fig. 8 A).

Distribution (
Fig. 26
): Andaman Islands**, Cambodia *, China , India , Indonesia : Java, Sumatra*, Myanmar *, Taiwan *, Thailand , Vietnam (* = new data; ** = no specimen examined in this study).
